ariants":[{"name":"Corbett","meanings":["English (West Midlands, of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>corbet</i> ‘raven’, probably denoting someone with dark hair or a dark complexion.","History: This is the name of a family descended from Hugh <i>Corbet</i>, a Norman baron who settled in Shropshire following the Norman Conquest. One of his descendants, Sir Richard Corbet, was granted land near Shrewsbury in 1223; since the 13th century, this place has been known as Moreton Corbet. The name was taken from Shropshire to Scotland in the 12th century and to northern Ireland in the 17th century, and thence to North America by at least one group of bearers of the name."]}]},{"name":"Alicia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Alisha","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."]},{"name":"Alisia","meanings":["Modern Latinate form of   Alice .  It was borne by the British ballerina  Alicia Markova  (born  Lilian Alicia Marks ,  1910–2004 )."]},{"name":"Alyssa","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alissa ."]},{"name":"Alissa","meanings":["Contracted form of   Alicia ."]},{"name":"Alesha","meanings":["Respelling of   Alicia ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":59,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":68,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":103,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Alicia Corbet was born in 1156, in Wattlesborough, Shropshire, England, her father, Walter Corbet, was 42 and her mother, Ana d'Umfraville, was 38. She married Thomas Bardolf Viscount of Bradewell in 1174, in Nottinghamshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in Kendal, Westmorland, England."},"et":{"1156–":"1156–Surnud","1156–Female":"1156–Surnud","1157–1208":"1157–1208","1141–Male":"1141–Surnud","–1272":"–1272","–Female":"Surnud","1180–1246":"1180–1246","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1114–1180":"1114–1180","1118–1185":"1118–1185","about 1180":"umbes 1180","1174":"1174","1185":"1185","1141":"1141","1272":"1272","1150":"1150","1180":"1180","1118":"1118","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1114":"1114","1246":"1246","1157":"1157","1156":"1156","1208":"1208","Kendal, Westmorland, England":"Kendal, Westmorland, England","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Pirton, Hertfordshire, England":"Pirton, Hertfordshire, England","Mackerston Roxburgh Scotland":"Roxburghshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Wattlesborough, Shropshire, England":"Wattlesborough, Shropshire, England","Kingston Russell, Dorset, England":"Kingston Russell, Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1156–":"1156–Kuollut","1156–Female":"1156–Kuollut","1157–1208":"115